# <type>: <subject>
# |<---- Using a maximum of 50 characters ---->|
#
# <body>
# |<---- Using a maximum of 72 characters ---->|
#
# <footer>
#
# Type can be:
#    feat     (new feature)
#    fix      (bug fix)
#    refactor (refactoring code)
#    style    (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
#    doc      (changes to documentation)
#    test     (adding or refactoring tests; no production code change)
#    chore    (updating build tasks, package configs, etc; no production code change)
#
# Subject should use imperative tone and not end with a period
# Example: feat: add payment method validation
#
# The body should include the motivation for the change and contrast with previous behavior
#
# The footer should contain any information about Breaking Changes and reference GitHub issues
# Example: Closes #123, #245, #992
#
# BREAKING CHANGE: <description of the breaking change>
